.TH "read_dt_param" 9 "read_dt_param" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
read_dt_param \- helper function for reading required parameters from the DT
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" read_dt_param
.BI "(struct tegra_dfll *td "  ","
.BI "const char *param "  ","
.BI "u32 *dest "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "td" 12
DFLL instance
.IP "param" 12
DT property name
.IP "dest" 12
output pointer for the value read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read a required numeric parameter from the DFLL device node, or complain
if the property doesn't exist. Returns a boolean indicating success for
easy chaining of multiple calls to this function.
